{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The library is now 100% Swift 6 compatible, and has been done in a way that is full backwards"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"compatible. If your project does not have strict concurrency warnings turned on, then updating"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the Composable Architecture to 1.15.0 should not cause any compilation errors. However, if you have"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"strict concurrency turned on, then you may come across a few situations you need to update."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Enum cases as function references","anchor":"Enum-cases-as-function-references"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is common to use the case of enum as a function, such as mapping on an ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Effect"},{"text":" to bundle","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"its output into an action:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["return client.fetch()","  .map(Action.response)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In strict concurrency mode this may fail with a message like this:","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"🛑 Converting non-sendable function value to ‘@Sendable (Value) -> Action’ may introduce data races"}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"There are two ways to fix this. You can either open the closure explicitly instead of using","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Action.response"},{"type":"text","text":" as a function:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["return client.fetch()","  .map { .response($0) }"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is also an upcoming Swift feature that will fix this. You can enable it in an SPM package"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by adding a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enableUpcomingFeature"},{"text":" to its Swift settings:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["swiftSettings: [","  .enableUpcomingFeature(\"InferSendableFromCaptures\"),","]),"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"And you can "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/blog\/using-upcoming-feature-flags\/","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"by navigating to your project’s build settings in Xcode, and adding a new “Other Swift Flags” flag:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["-enable-upcoming-feature InferSendableFromCaptures"]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.15"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The library has been completely updated for Swift 6 language mode, and now compiles in strict"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"concurrency with no warnings or errors.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"metadata":{"title":"Migrating to 1.15","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture